In large stainless steel saucepan or Dutch oven, combine bones, water, wine, peppercorns, parsley, leek, celery, bay leaf and thyme. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, skimming surface if necessary. Pour through sieve. Discard solids. To freeze: Let stock cool. Refrigerate. Ladle into freezer containers. Seal, label and date. Freeze for up to 3 months. To serve: Thaw stock in microwave or in refrigerator overnight.